GROUP.DESCRIPTION: Recap claims still participate in RTMD so these claims need the data lookup to occur for them on the EDW1 source. Recap claims are supposed to finish migrating to RXC in 2017, and after they are fully migrated then the lookup and associated transformations can be removed.
GROUP.NAME: RECAP

GROUP.DESCRIPTION: Non-Recap claims will never find data on the lookup, and could have these fields filled from the input file.
GROUP.NAME: NON_RECAP

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION:
This router will use the EXTL_SRC_CD to determine whether or not the claim is sourced from Recap.
Recap data will continue come from the EDW1 until the Recap clients are fully migrated to RXC and no longer flowing through that adjudication engine. While we are still processing Recap (primarily FEP) we need to continue to do RTMD data lookups. Since the claim Recap claim is sourced from EDW1, the RTMD fields need to also be from that source.
RXC clients are the other RTMD participants, but as of July 2017 their claims and RTMD data will be sourced from PBMDW and the RTMD fields will be sent to Rebates on the PBMDW claim extract for RXC, no need to lookup the values. That is why when an RXC claim comes through this mapping, the RTMD fields have already been populated (if the claim participates) and that data needs to be moved from the source to the target, as-is.
No other claim sources participate in RTMD, and should not do the lookup on EDW1.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: RTR_RTMD_Lookup_Claims

GROUP.DESCRIPTION: Path for the data when none of the group conditions are satisfied.
